A YOUNG amateur footballer has died from his injuries after a car crash.
Dale Whillans, 18, was a passenger in a Seat which left the road and ended up in a field on Monday.
He was taken to Borders General Hospital then transferred to Edinburgh Royal Infirmary. He lost his fight for life in the Western General yesterday.
The accident happened on the A698 at Timpendean, near Jedburgh. Another passenger was badly injured while the 18-year-old driver suffered minor injuries.
Dale, from Hawick, played for Border Amateur League side Hawick Legion.
A statement on their Facebook page said everyone at the club was devastated. It added: “Dale will be sorely missed not just by everyone at the club but by the town of Hawick as a whole.”
